{
  "stem": "22856.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I survived it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In these wagons which we had received from Brunnlitz, from Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The same wagons were for us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, probably it was a Czechoslovakian machinist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But anyway, we were traveling without any guard.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We could take into our wagon everything what we wanted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have much.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was only one rucksack with some personal things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It is worthwhile to mention that Schindler provided for us with some material for clothing and other things, which were amassed in the-- in the storeroom, so that everybody had something to keep.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember from that material I could make one suit and overcoat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And from wool, the girls started to prepare some cardigans, who was clever enough.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In some cases, we received some cigarettes, some drinks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I heard, also, that Schindler provided arms for us, in case if we were, in the last moment, surrounded by the German, that we had arms to defend ourselves.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it never came to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we knew that he went to Americans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And later on, there came messages by correspondence that he is in Germany, and that Jews are caring for him.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was that-- by that time, sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They arranged for him some medical.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We knew that later on we were collecting some money for Mrs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Schindler.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I received even from her letter a letter to thank for the money which we sent.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But she was cared by higher authorities.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We know that she received a, a widow pension from Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the B'nai Brith arranged for her a house, as long as she lives.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She was provided, after all, she hasn't got a great demand now.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She's over 90.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
